[[File:Matti Milius - Peeter Mudist.JPG|right|thumb|Peeter Mudist (left) with art dealer Matti Milius]] '''Peeter Mudist''' (19 April 1942, [[Tallinn]] – 6 December 2013) was an [[Estonia]]n painter, sculptor, and [[print-maker]] whose works have received multiple awards.<ref name="Postimees">{{cite news|url=http://www.postimees.ee/2622520/suri-kunstnik-peeter-mudist|title=Suri kunstnik Peeter Mudist|last=Einmann |first=Andres|date=December 6, 2013|publisher=[[Postimees]]|language=Estonian|accessdate=6 December 2013}}</ref><ref name="einst">{{cite web |url=http://www.einst.ee/Ea/2_03/newbooks.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-08-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060927204934/http://www.einst.ee/Ea/2_03/newbooks.html |archivedate=2006-09-27 |df= }}</ref><ref name="invis">{{cite web |url=http://www.hot.ee/siramsiram/invisibl.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-08-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613135845/http://www.hot.ee/siramsiram/invisibl.html |archivedate=2011-06-13 |df= }}</ref> He was also a member of the [[Estonian Artists' Union]].<ref name="invis"/>
==Early life== Born in 1942,<ref name="einst"/> in [[Tallinn]], Mudist studied painting at the [[Estonian State Art Institute]] for 4 years, starting in 1963.<ref name="invis"/>
==Later life and death== Mudist had [[Parkinson's Disease]] in his later years.<ref name="invis"/> He died on the morning of 6 December 2013.{{citation needed|date=December 2013}}
==Awards== * [[Baltic Assembly Prize for Literature, the Arts and Science]] (1995)
